SIMPLE: sinch
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sinch
<hw>Sinch</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Cinch</er>.]</ety> <def>A saddle girth made of leather, canvas,
woven horsehair, or woven grass.</def> <mark>[Western U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sinch</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sinch
<hw>Sinch</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To gird with a sinch; to tighten
the sinch or girth of (a saddle); <as>as, to <ex>sinch</ex> up a
sadle</as>.</def> <mark>[Western U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sincipital</ent>⟦br⟧
